{
  "texts": [
    "2015 also marked the emergence of many anti-immigrant social media groups, blogs and online news and opinion portals which have gained popularity since then.",
    "This includes the radical right online news portal Uued Uudised, a channel whose news are often ideologically in line with and give voice to the political party of EKRE (\"Conservative People's Party of Estonia\").",
    "In academic literature EKRE has often been classified as a radical right populist party [22,[24][25][26][27] whilst the party describes itself as national conservative [26,28].",
    "Uued Uudised has been described as both alternative [22] as well as hyper partisan media [28].",
    "It was established in 2015 during the EU immigration crisis."
  ]
}